message:
A clean init for Caffe2, removing my earlier hacky
commits.
delete unused pb file.

Simplify the data sharing mechanism, using std::shared_ptr instead of home-brew code.

Also cleaned notebook notes a little bit.
fix an embarrassing bug introduced when moving over the padding change.
Caffe translator example notebook, and some nicety-type changes that accompany it.
bottlefeeding.
GoogleNet adaption - added yet another legacy padding support.
enable optional_deps so that any non-crucial failures will not break the whole system.
namespace google -> gflags for gflags functions.
explicitly make end_to_end_test depend on core_gpu
More flag changes… and adding back run_plan_mpi
Adding <memory> to the header. Clang is fine with missing this but gcc complains.
Fix some bug in the old code: the net device option overwite used to not work.
[pycaffe2] net_drawer: do not exit too loud if pydot is not present.
[LegacySupport] Fixed a bug in the caffe pooling case: pad_tail is changed on first run so we can only use pad_head for the legacy padding value.
[minor] net.cc: in parallelnet, if the user forgot to set a num_workers, warn instead of quitting.
[style] Massive name change from plural to singular. This one changes operator’s “inputs” and “outputs” to “input” and “output”, and "args" to "arg".
[style] Finishing name changes for the rest of the fields in the protobuf.
minor format issue

Merge pull request #1 from xiaoyunwu/master

minor format issue
[interface] OperatorBase::OutputIsType
[op] iter_op: instead of producing an int, produces it in a wrapped tensor.
rerun mnist notebook, due to interface change.
workspace: create root folder if not exist.
[bugfix] missing dependency
[bugfix] static initialization order fiasco.

Some non-trivial refactoring:

(1) added blob serialization.
(2) registry can now use key types other than string.
(3) changed load_save_op so they interface with a db.
(4) change sgd iter op: it does increments so we can resume an iter.
(5) mnist linear classifier tests snapshot functionality.
(6) added protodb which is a small wrapper over TensorProtos.
[build] flush output from subprocesses
[binaries] add missing header

Merge pull request #2 from longjon/master

Bring in Jon's changes.
make things compile for gcc
zmqdb: make clear error message that zmq 3+ is required.
Update license and readme.

Several changes:

[misc] Update license and readme.

[binary] some enhancement to move over caffe databases.

[python] added an alexnet2 example notebook.

(1) minidb bugfix
(2) blob serialization comments
(3) cudnn: putting it under a separate device name
    so we can explicitly choose cudnn instead of
    having CUDA device prioritizing it.
(4) note that mint is not available with ipython
    due to zeromq conflict
(5) db_throughput utility
(6) added gprofiler
Use c++ to do zmqdb, and added a simple zmq feeder example.
zmqdb: pass key as well.
zmq feeder: catch error when setting up the socket.
zmq feeder bugfix
minor change
Some more MPI examples
Add an execution chain option to force operator orders.
conv_op: during backward, bias is not needed.
run_plan_mpi: check the returned state
broadcast op: it is an in-place op with both input and output set
legacy names due to the plural->singular change
bugfix
core_gradients change that goes with conv gradient change
reorg mpi_ops
blob templating
